# Evolve rules when the codebase patterns change

Trigger this when **writing or reviewing code**, not only when editing rule files.

## Consider a rule change when

- A new pattern appears that no rule mentions.
- The same shape is copied across several files.
- Recurring bugs or review comments could be prevented with a short standard.
- A library or tool becomes the default in multiple places.
- Security, performance, or testing conventions stabilize.

## How

- Compare new code with current rules in `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/`.
- Prefer one focused rule per topic; don't bloat unrelated ones.
- Pull examples from real repo code.
- Cross-link related rules instead of duplicating paragraphs.

For **how** to author rule files, see [write-cursor-rules-for-this-project.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ai-rules/write-cursor-rules-for-this-project.mdc).
For **deprecation, quality, and doc sync**, see [maintain-cursor-rules.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/ai-rules/maintain-cursor-rules.mdc).
